caption: Was a great time as always. Burger and beer is bomb along with an awesome night of trivia! Nick hosts a great night of fun if you’re free on a Wednesday. See you again next week.

First experience today at wednesday trivia was unexpected. I was having a good time with a group of friends. During trivia, two groups, one including me, went up to subtly and politely call into question one of the answers. The trivia host Nick then preceded to unnecessarily embarrass me on the mic. Big Top Brewing Company is a great time, but don’t expect a friendly environment for trivia night with Nick.

BUFFALO CAULIFLOWER BITES. They are super unique and delicious!! Not like bbq like some, but very yummy!! Suuuper friendly amazing staff ❤ great beer, great location, great vibes ☺🍻

Come for the beer and stay for the food!  Not only do they offer beer in all kinds of amazing flavors they offer more than just bar food.  Stop by and enjoy everything Big Top has to offer; you won't be disappointed.
Management is awesome. Food is delicious and loved the bottomless mimosas for brunch. Even enjoyed the games available for our large group!
It's an ok place. Last time I went they could not get a food order right for anything. Good selection on beer though.

Love Big Top Pensacola so we wanted to try this one.  Got there 4:10 and the sign said bar service only but when we got to the bar they said they were closing at 4:30 so we would have to drink our beers fast.  We walked out and a block away the place we went was packed

We were visiting from out of town and stumbled upon this pub. It's a nice local hang out spot. It's a bit of a college crowd. They had live music and good selection of craft beers.

Food was great, amazing service, would recommend.

Food was pretty good here and I only had a couple of the beers, and I usually don't like beer but they had a couple that I really liked. They have a unique variety of beers to choose from and to satisfy most tastes, including mine.
Great wings and tacos.  Pleasant wait staff.  We would definitely go back.
Beer ok. Food okay. Service not good. Need better organized seating. Very loud. Probably just good place for a beer, but not dinner.

I want to like this place as the beer is pretty good. However, the last two times I’ve been the service has been quite bad. First time we had dinner and the food took a long time to come out. The server never came by to check on us so we had to find a different server to order more beers. Then just yesterday I went in for a drink around 11. The place was half empty but all the tables still had empty plates, glasses, etc. on them with nobody seeming to make an effort to clean up. Stood around for about 5 minutes before leaving to go somewhere else.

Eh, it’s alright. Great spot tho!!!

They have great local brewed beer and amazing food
Good food, good beer.  They have fun events.
Decent food, just don't come for lunch if you have a job.  You'll be late getting back to work even if there are very few customers.
Great place for a Brew. Moe and Bob are the bee's knees! Cheers! Like IPAs? Check out my Instagram: eric_loves_IPA

I was at this place today today. As a matter of fact I went there while I was waiting for someone to pick me up and had a big plate of french fries I love their fries. The place is very nice inside very pleasant very friendly.
Great food and tasty (though small) list of beer.

Went there for brunch today. Our party ordered, some ordering the bottomless mimosas. Two of us never got glasses for the mimosas and after about 30 mins had to go up to the bar and ask for some as the waiter was pretty scarcely seen. We all ordered food and waited an hour and a half until the food finally came out. My omelet actually never came out so I just had them remove it from our ticket. My wife's french toast was a single slice, which is a pretty small portion for the price.  Went a while back just for drinks and a snack. The beer was good, but the pretzel sticks were obviously microwaved.  Seems like they are just not a good place to go for food.
Great selections! Good vibe! I'll be back.

Awesome people, great atmosphere, and fantastic beer! I'm obsessed with the Hawaiian Lion Porter any many others! They also have the best breakfast burrito I've ever had! I love everything about this place! I highly recommend it!
Fun local brewery, with good food.

Excellent place to unwind after work. The bartenders are super friendly and knowledgeable. If you like hazys IPA I highly recommend the Highwire. Their food menu has options for everyone including classic bar food like burgers and wings to vegetarian  options like fried avocado tacos.
The food was very good and creative for a tap room. The customer service was spot on too. However, the beer was not as impressive. I guess, I'm ok coming back but it's not a priority for me.
Good food and large selection of brews.
Chill beer spot with a sizable grub selection
Good food, nice selection of beers. Live music was great.

Staff was friendly and helpful.  Beer selection was awesome.  Food was pretty good.  Finding free parking is difficult. Definately worth a visit and open on mondays.
Great beer, Interesting act, super helpful friendly female bartender.
Great food and great drinks. Specials throughout the week, check their FB

The beer is decent. Like that they offered flights. The food however is horrible. Appetizers are severely overpriced for the minimal amount you received. And everything was bland. The beer cheese that came with two separate appetizers was basically the burnt lumpy chunks from the bottom of pot. We returned and even though the replacements looked better, they tasted just as bad. There is a reason breweries don't serve food. This place should stick to beer only
Good food, great beer, and games in the back
Great beer, good food.
Cool place to have beers and wings

Awesome selection of beers on tap and the service here is outstanding. Adrian always takes great care of us and his entire staff has a pleasant/light/fun attitude which makes coming here very enjoyable. Definitely recommend stopping by when you are in town.
Glad we stopped in, Adrian the bartender took his time to explain all the beers and make sure we got the one that we liked the most. Thank you dude!
Really delicious brunch! Bottomless momosas for 8 dollars are incredible. No vegan options for brunch other than sides.
Great place, even better beers.  Moe is the man knew exactly what I'd like.  Definitely coming back!
Great beer and food.  Friendly staff.
Great

Let me very clear, these are the BEST tacos I have had in probably all my life. It is almost impossible to find a brewery/bar with good food, but this goes beyond that. The fish and brisket tacos are something of another planet. The place is welcoming and the staff is friendly. The beer of course is amazing, but as bizarre as this might sound, the food steals the show.

A really nice location, very open, inviting.  Staff was very friendly & quite up-to-speed on all their offerings. Parking is easier to find than the home - Sarasota - location but could require a trip around the block. The beer is made on-site, not shipped up. Good and fresh & flavorful. A nice addition to an area that doesn't have as many breweries as you'd expect a college town to have.

I work overnights so this place was awesome to stop by for a good lunch and beer after a long night. Moe is awesome - been awhile since ive been back due to drinking every beer on the menu, but have heard their list has changed since the last time ive been. Regardless of this fact this is easily an up and coming brewery in Gainesville and the food is so good. If youre like me and eat two filling meals a day go for the Daredevil Totchos as they are easily the most filling and delicious thing on the menu. The burgers are also very good along with the Cuban.
Beer is okay. Food not good. Hamburger bun and quesadilla very burnt. Not good.
Great food, service was slow.
Great place!

Went to Brunch on 7/7 and enjoyed the food. I ordered the Burrito and it was delicious! The only downside to the restaurant/brewery was the staff. Our friends arrived at 10am and the place was not set up and it took around 10 to 15 minutes once I arrived to just get water. I had several servers during the meal and between the three of them, one mumbled, the other forget to bring silverware after saying hed be back, and the third had the same issues with a box to bring home my leftovers and gave an attitude when we asked for the bill.  Maybe they were short staffed or underprepared for the crowd(we were the first group there at opening), but overall the service made me uncomfortable. Food and beer is good, poor service 2/5.
Good beer, plenty of options. Great pricing. Intuitive bartenders and very very friendly. Very clean and new facilities. 10/10 recommendation
So much fun! They have a foosball table in the back and food trucks parked out front and the beers I had were very good!
Had the Sunday brunch. Food was excellent!
Friendly, decent beer.
Great atmosphere.  Great service.

AC was not working so it was real hot. Ordered an appetizer and received the wrong one. We got asked if we wanted to keep it anyways which we all thought implied it would be free. We got charged for both even after asking to verify with a manager.

We ordered pork wonton as an appetizer.  Our waiter eventually came to our table with a plate of oyster bruschetta.  We explained that wasn’t what we ordered. He apologized and said it was his mistake, and that he “probably pressed a wrong button”.  He offered us the app anyways.  When we got our checks, our waiter asked us how we wanted to split the bruschetta.  He never explained that the app would be added to our bill. I’ve never had to pay for something I didn’t order at a restaurant before, so I was surprised we were being asked about it.  He said he would ask his manager, who apparently wasn’t immediately present, about the situation.  The waiter came back a few minutes later and told us his manager said we need to pay for the appetizer, which again we did not order, and explained to us that we were wrong because “we could have said no and I could’ve thrown it away instead”.  On top of that, the AC was broken the entire time and we were told it needed to be looked at every 4 days or so.  Beer was pretty good but I won’t go back and wouldn’t recommend this place.
Great brewery!

Incredible beers and unbelievable offerings! PLEASE check this place out, they have daily specials and also chef specials. They also have Sunday Brunch!!! The Cuban Burger and the Smoking Cannon wowwwwwwww
The atmosphere was relaxing, the service and food were really great. They have plenty of beer on tap whether you like ipas or a nice Porter. You should go and check them out!

Some great Big top beers and guest taps.  Service was quick and friendly.  Beautiful building and pet friendly.  Great burgers and the pretzel sticks w/poblano cheese are fantastic.  This is our second Big Top location we have visited and it does not disappoint.  We will be back!
Nice staff with great beer and food.
Cool spot. Plenty of beer options. Beer quality was alright but service was good. Bob was great!
Love this place. Great food too

Beer is great. Food is good. Server is chatty. Beware of automatic 25% tip added to bill regardless of party size. You can move the tip up or down (it isn't easy to do and you have to do it before you insert your card), but they don't tell you that it is already on there, so it would be super easy to accidentaly double tip. They have an updated menu with a bunch of new items as of this week (5/20) and the wait staff seems to not quite know them all yet. Also, it was really weird when my friend's Cesar salad came with the dressing on the side. I definitely would go back for the beer, however! I had two of their brews that were amazingly delicious. And while I might snag an appetizer, I'd probably walk down the street for supper.
Got the fish and chips along with some roasted cauliflower bites. Both were really good! The mint sauce that came with the cauliflower bites was really tasty!
Not sure why I've held out to check this place out.  Had good beers and the Fire Eater sandwich.  Really good.  Good and friendly service.  Will def be back.

Like music.

The best part about this place is the hand soap!! It smells like Bath and Body Works Sweet Pea. I mean, the taco tuesdays are amazing too. I love all of them, and I love that you can mix and match. We always have the same server every week and we love him. He’s funny and so kind. The beers are nice, but the beer vats- just decoration. Deceiving but very decorative. Overall, I love coming here for the atmosphere and beer and food specials.
Cute place...some people were eating. We just stopped for a beer.

Awesome place. Friendly people. Great place for out of towners like ourselves.

Went for Trivia Night! Fun, open atmosphere with community table style seating and a moderate selection of beers including many of their originals. Full kitchen and friendly staff! Close to the heart of downtown Gainesville, and within walking distance of many other spots!

Although they haven't started brewing their own beer beer yet, the beer was phenomenal. It was bought from their headquarters in Sarasota. Great atmosphere, clean, and friendly staff. Great beers...the best I found from a micro brewery.

Love this brewery. Exactly what downtown needed. Great beer and pretty good food. The business is still new but I have had nothing but good experiences. Bartenders are knowledgeable and willing to let you taste and even mix certain beers... ie their version of a Black and Tan. Certain nights are busier than others depending on the specials but great location and easy way to start a night out or have dinner with friends.

This will most likely change to a 5 star. Luckily you can get 6packs of their core beers at grocery and liquor stores. Next time I'm in Gainesville I will stop here again.

Food and drinks and service was terrible!!! Saw food being prepared without gloves!!! Drinking glasses was dirty!!! Restrooms dirty, saw pest crawling around!!! I wouldn’t recommend this place to no one!!! I got sick after eating there!!!
Great beer selection. Close to all restaurants in dowtown area. Service is amazing. Great patio.
Everyone liked the beers they tried. Prices were pretty good.

I am a big fan of Big Top Brewing’s beers from the Sarasota location, so I was very excited to hear they were coming to Gainesville.  The brewery had its grand opening on the day we went. It was busy, but not to the point that we couldn’t move around. There was tasteful live music playing inside. Bar games were availability including a couple arcade games and giant connect 4. A few TVs are scattered around the walls of the brewery. The main room is cozy and makes good use of the space. It too cold outside for us to venture into the beer garden, but there was outside seating available.  We sat at a table where one of the staff members happily waited on us. We tried a few of the beers, the “totchos”, and a burger with bacon jam. I can safely say everything was delicious. All of the beers we tried were awesome and we look forward to trying even more. Our waitress was attentive and friendly despite how busy the brewery was.  Overall, Big Top’s new Gainesville location might become our new favorite spot to have casual drinks in downtown. Great space, atmosphere, food, and of course beer.

Great place with a good beer selection. Their brown ales are the best in Gainesville. Cool looking modern brewery with multiple TV's. They also have food now.

Went in for lunch, decided to work the rest of the day from the bar. It has a good selection of classic rock music playing, isn't over crowded, the beer is good, and the food is decent.  Fish-sticks and fries $6. It wasn't "OMG best food ever" but is about the same price as a Mcdonalds meal so... for that reason i'd call it a win.
Just ate at Dragonfly and walked by the newly opened brewery just behind. I look forward to spending more time there and sampling more beers great vibe and feel!
